title.narrative: IR 5.3 ADOLESCENT CONSTRUCTIVE ENGAGEM

description.narrative: 5.3 By end 2014, 30,000 adolescent boys and girls are engaged in commu nity level knowledge generation and social mobilization for their peers., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Human Rights Institutions, Skills Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 5: By 2014, capacities of national partners and service facilities are developed to promote civic engagement, participation, knowledge and skills of 135,000 boys and girls aged 10 to 18 to support the transition from childhood to adulthood.
